======== Colon Commands ========

:args					Show args to vim
:edit <filename>			Edit filename in place

:global :g/pattern/{command}		Run command on pattern.

:saveas <filename>			Save current text as filename
:set
	ic
	patchmode
:syntax
	enable
:help
:options
:color <color>


======== Splitting Windows ========

	-------- Open --------

		:new			Horizontally split a new empty window.
		:split			Horizontally split a new window to current file.
		:split <filename>	Horizontally split a new window to <filename>.


		:vnew			Vertically split a new empty window.
		:vsplit			Vertically split a new window to current file.
		:vsplit <filename>	Vertically split a new window to <filename>.


	-------- Close --------

		:close			Close current window.
		:only			Close all but current window.


	-------- Move and Navigate --------


		CTRL-W <direction arrow>	Move to window in <direction arrow>
		CTRL-W < H | J | K | L >	Move window to LEFT(H), BOTTOM(J), TOP(K), or RIGHT(L).


	-------- Size --------

		[#] CTRL-W +	Increase size 1 or # lines
		[#] CTRL-W -	Decrease size 1 or # lines
                # CTRL-W _	Set window size to # lines


======== Tabbed Windows ========

	:tab split				Create a new tab editing the current file.
	:tab split <filename>			Create a new tab editing <filename>.

	gt					Cycle through tabs

	


======== Letter Commands ========

p	paste
yy	yank a line


======== Modes ========

       	-------- Visual Mode --------
   
   		Colon commands operate on visual selection
   
   	-------- Visual Block Mode --------

		$				Select to end of all lines.
		I{text}<Esc>			Insert text on all lines.
		A{text}<Esc>			Append text to end of selected lines.
		~				Swap case
		U				Make selection uppercase
		u				Make selection lowercase
		>				Shift selection 1 amount.
		<				Remove shift 1 amount.
	


======== vimdiff ========


	:set noscrollbind		Turn off scroll binding


	do				diff obtain
	dp				diff put
